    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-02T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-02T04:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3234: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sammons</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-02T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received October 2, 10.30 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tong Shao-yi, Chief of Southern Peace Delegation, disgusted with both Northern
                    and Southern military party tactics, sent official seal and resignation to
                        latter.<note n="59" xml:id="d346fn59">For report of the refusal to accept
                        his resignation, see <ref target="#pg_396">p. 396</ref>.</note> Legation
                    notified.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sammons</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
